This paper proposes a new search strategy for optimization problems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The proposed approach involves manipulating arrays of fitness values, which is a data structure topic relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on benchmark problems, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO).
